WHEREAS, the museum serves as a valuable community resource that connects
families to regional experts and expertise, strengthens family bonds, and prepares
Louisiana's youngest learners for future success.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby designate Monday, April 13, 2026, as Knock Knock Children's Museum Day
at the Louisiana State Capitol and commends the museum for its outstanding contributions
to early childhood education, community engagement, and economic development in
Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Senate expresses its appreciation for the
museum's ongoing mission to be a community spark for engaging, playful learning
experiences that inspire and support lifelong learning, and in opening doors for children to
a world of opportunity and possibility.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
chairman of the board, Alexandra Layfield, and the executive director of the Knock Knock
Children's Museum.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
